Albert Webb, 51, and sons Jimmy Chuter, 26, and Jesse Webb, 19, followed people aged up to 97 home from the Post Office .
They followed them in a silver Mercedes C200 until they got close to their homes .
The trio would drive alongside their victims in a Mercedes before telling them they had come to collect payment for roofing work .
In total, the gang carried out 35 thefts, starting in February 2012 - when pensioners were still able to withdraw money from their local Post Office accounts .